<br>
1) Pet resists. Serious issue when dealing with AOE mobs, why aren't pets TOTALLY immune to their specific resisted element? Fire pets ARE immune to fire, but earth is only highly resistant to disease, same for air vs. cold, water vs poison.<br>
Epic pet has poor resists, why when it's meant to be the best of ALL? Why has no pet got good MAGIC resist? Epic has decent MR but not HIGH.<br>
<br>
2) Charms on pets. Pets almost NEVER resist charms, in PvP this is seriously imbalancing, and every time a pet gets charmed you may get the &quot;player can only have one pet at a time&quot; bug. I don't mind ME getting charmed, but it's *extremely* frustrating when doing a BoTB someone cheated, used charms and almost EVERY pet you make gets charmed.<br>
<br>
3) Mob resists. Mages get no cold, disease or poison nukes, and no lures, I can understand why if it's to do with game balancing but it IS annoying as hell, especially in places where you can't use pets. Despite recent changes I STILL wouldnt use a pet in TOV, PoH2 or VP, the risk is far too great, and many of the mobs are immune to our nukes. I didn't play a mage to be a &quot;rod monkey&quot; :&gt;<br>
Would a nuke that summons a bolt, a meteor or such that hits versus AC, not resists be so unbalancing? make it have  not such a great mana/damage ratio, as per wiz Lures, but do decent damage. A frequently over looked point is that not every mage is lvl 60 and every mob Maloed/tash/Ro's, low lvl mages get a hell of a time nuking many raid mobs, Naggy for example.<br>
  --Is this an issue, though?--<br>
<br>
4) Monster Summoning 3, Greater Vocerate Air still need damage upgraded in light of other pet changes. Could the Monster Summoning sries be made more useful, summoning an actual mob? Make the MS pets not affected by Burnout and mage pet heals since they are not elementals, would that make a useful pet? Would it be imbalanced? Should it use an expensive reagant? Would that counter the worry on Dire Charmed pets?<br>
<br>
5) Would it be better for the earth, air and water Vocerates/greater Vocerates to PROC their spells, rather than cast them?<br>
Can pets' lousy proc rates be improved? Note that pets have problems landing spells on high level mobs!<br>
   --Is this an issue, though?--<br>
<br>
6) Would the ability to summon weapons that proc stuns and a variety of DDs, maybe snare, be of use to improve pets?<br>
Would we want to be able to summon weapons useful to PLAYERS? Since the nerf on the Sword of Runes, mage weapons aren't really wanted by players, and are only marginally useful to pets in a very few situations (AOEs and the Hole specifically)<br>
  --Is this an issue, though?--<br>
<br>
7) It seems pets have a haste cap of 60% making high level buffs/Muzzle of Mardu redundant, this is a SERIOUS oversight and needs fixed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Frenzied Burnout needs drastically improved. It should work <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> exactly as advertised</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> with ATK, haste and Flurries, BUT, the duration should be 10 minutes, otherwise its worthless.<br>
<br>
9) Damage Shields seem weak at higher levels, considering the amount of hit points mobs have. Considering at low level you get a damage shield that does 5hp, when facing mobs that do 10-20hp, then at high level you get a 33hp damage shield against mobs doing 100-200hp!<br>
Shouldn't high level damage shield be 50hp as per Fire pets/epic?<br>
   --Is this an issue, though?--<br>
<br>
10) Call of the Hero should NOT be thought of by Verant as some kind of &quot;cheat&quot; to bypass content. Without it, many raids simply CANNOT HAPPEN, because an online game with players from across the world has a HELLISH TIME COORDINATING when people can join up to play! The coffin summon thing is total stupid waste of time, xp and money, players HATE it, it's imbecilic! verant needs ot change its attitude to CoH, it's as vital to raids as Rez and TLs, seriously!<br>
  By all means, disable CoH in spots you need a Key to get to, so as to prevent exploits, except Sky. Sky sucks, sky sucks HUGELY because of the problems with keys and no CoH, hasn't Verant noted its the most underused and generally most loathed zone in the game? Not that the zone isn't interesting or fun, just the hassles involved with it make for a very stressful raid.<br>
<br>
11) Some parts of the epic still need fixed. Phinigel Autropos should ALWAYS drop a random epic item, bards, mages, wizards and rogues all need him, one pal killed him <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> FIFTY SIX TIMES!!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to get his mage staff, that's totally bonkers on a 12 hour spawn mob who's a pain to do!<br>
Why Isle 7? If sky was less of a hassle to do, that wouldn't be so bad, but currently it's a MASSIVE pain and very few folk EVER go to Isle 7.<br>
<br>
12) The Focus staffs are too rare and hard to get, considering that apart from 2 being used in the epic, they are one of the few MAJOR upgrades a mage can get. The Air Staff *still* needs the same crown as the epic AND is so hard to complete its almost as hard as the epic itself!<br>
Magi P'Tasi, Mistress of Scorn should ALWAYS have Earth and Fire staffs. As noted Phinigel should ALWAYS drop one of the 4 epic items, and a mob in Sky should ALWAYS drop the Air staff.<br>
<br>
13) The Mass group Buff ability for mages seems almost useless, as we only get 2 group spells, both damage shields. Something more useful is surely needed? What about a full PARTY CoH? Summons the entire party to the mage? or an across zone CoH? Or something else? Any ideas? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
