<br>
Let me first start by saying I think the pet improvements were good, and well deserved.  I agree, there is much left to do.  <br>
<br>
Due to the fact that I attend many high end raids, some form of nuke variety is important to me.  This may not be the case for everyone depending on level and what they do with their time.  I do think we need a variety of nukes, ie cold, poison or something.  SoFB is a decent spell but not what we should get at 60, it need to do more damage, especially with the lack of cold, poison, disease based nukes.  <br>
<br>
Mana regen is a also a problem I have.  Wizards through familiars get much more mana regen.  Even though there only offensive ability is nukes, and we have pets, it's still somewhat unbalanced in my opinion.  Transon's should have 6/tick of mana regen.<br>
<br>
FT items need to be more widely available for all casters, at level 60 we have a pretty massive mana pool, and this is an inequality with casters vs melee.  While melees have continued to do more and more damage with post 60 levels, we continue to basically med at the same rate with increased mana pools, therefore, taking longer.  Like I said, FT is a good thing and needs to be made more widely available, even if it's in the form of FT 1 items.<br>
<br>
Summons, I don't want any more trinket summons.  I realize we're the summoner type class, but it gets a bit much to summon people (via CoH), then summon focus items, then summon mod rods the rest of the raid.  You want to have me summon a big Meteor (like silver blade said) that has some effect on the mod, I'm cool with that.  Heck why not have some kind of group based summon, as I've seen previously someone suggest summon a wall of protection that would act like a DA type shield.  /shrug just a thought.<br>
<br>
Damage shields, yes I think these need to be increased.  33 points on some of these high end mobs isn't as effective as it could be.<br>
<br>
Class type AA abilities, come on now, these aren't that great, another example of VI not putting a lot of though into the game.  Water illusion needs to be upgraded just to mention 1.<br>
<br>
I love playing my mage, but after 2.5 years of it I've learned a few things... one of which is it could be THE best class in the game if VI would put some thought in to what they are doing.<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts. <p>Master Caldywen Lebeau <BR>
