<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Pet Haste Cap:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
This is currently set at 60%, making <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> above III nearly useless, along with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Muzzle of Mardu</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  This needs to be raised to 100-115%.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Fix Mage AA Class Skills:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Frenzied Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is broken, and would be unappealling even if fixed.  Even if it doubled pet damage output, it would be better just to let the pet fight for 36 seconds longer.  It is also not consisent with the theme of a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and the need to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;burn down&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a foe is better met by existing nukes.<br>
<br>
I propose a new skill, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Improved Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which adds +5 ATK per skill level times the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> level of the next cast of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  So a mage with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Improved Burnout 1</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> casting <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Burnout III</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would add +15 ATK, whereas a mage with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Improved Burnout 3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> casting <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Burnout IV</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would add +60 ATK.  The skill would have three levels, and cost either 3/6/9 or 5/10/15 AA.  As it would last 15 minutes, a refresh timer of 144 minutes seems fair.  It would allow <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Ancient Burnout V</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to someday function to provide a raid level pet.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Soft Thirties:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
There appears to be a weak spot in the 30's.  Adding a new more and more efficient pet heal at 29th level might add just enough back bone to get over the hump without having a dramatic effect.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Difficulty of Epic:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Oddly enough, I do not have a strong opinion on the difficulty of the epic.  No, I do not have my epic.  I agree that some parts are quite frustrating, but I can offer no suggestions here.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Pet Resist Rates:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
If we do indeed need to have more resistant pets, perhaps the following is a reasonable solution, as a 50+ spell.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Summon Belt of Elemental Protection</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: summons a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Belt of Elemental Protection</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which is RACE: NONE, CLASS: NONE <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  (meaning pets only)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, with plus 50 FR/DR/MR/CR/PR.  That might be sufficient to tip the scales.  It might also have some AC and HP.  It would have the advantage of only applying to prepared pets, not chain cast pets.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Mob Resists:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Frankly, I am content with my resist rate as I have experienced it so far, and do not desire to tread on the toes of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Wizards</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  As initially enamored as I was of the physical dart idea, saving against AC instead of MR, we already have one: it's called a pet.  I would rather solve pet problems and use those instead of invent a new class of spell, or get a cold or whatever based nuke.<br>
<br>
If such a bolt is deemed viable, then the easiest way to implement it without adding new game mechanics might be to add <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Summon Javelin of Destruction</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which is NO RENT, NO DROP, LORE, goes in the archery slot, is based off <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Throwing Skill</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, has a +100 ATK bonus <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  (so it might actually hit)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and does 500 damage, so it might be worthwhile.  Those numbers are off the top of my head, and might now be viable, but they avoid coding for a new kind of spell or resistance by abusing existing game mechanics.<br>
<br>
On a raid, I have three things I can do, and adapt according to the mob.  I can nuke, I can pet, and I can rod.  At least one of those things is likely to be useful.  While rodding may be tedious, so are the many of the roles others are required to fulfill on raids.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Left Behind Pets:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I do think <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Greater Vocaration: Air</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Monster Summoning 3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> should have their damage scaled up to keep in line with the other level 57+ pet spells.  However, we might want to test and see if the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Air</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pet is already stunning more.  It appears to me as if this might be the case, and if so, an increase in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  GV:Air</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> damage output might not be justified.  The disadvantages of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  MS3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> however, in particular the inability to equip weapons, suggests to me that an increase in damage output is justified and fair.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Damage Shields:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I am not dissatisfied with them, except a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Druid</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> should never get a better damage shield than ours, even if they do worship <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Karana</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  As they are, under most circumstances, damage shields are incredibly mana efficient, and cannot be resisted.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Slow</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> reduces their value, but so what?  Some improved damage shields might be icing on the cake, but hardly critical, I think.<br>
<br>
I agree that a long lasting, kick butt damage shield at level 60 might provide some lacking oomph among our level 60 spells.  Where <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>is</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> our <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  KEI</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, our 60th level spell that people seek us out for?  Nowhere now.  If it were group, it might even make <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Mass Group Buff</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> worth while.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Summoned Proccing Weapons:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
More icing, except perhaps as NONE/NONE pet only weapons to address pet deficiencies, and there are alternatives.  We do have nice summons, the focus items remain quite valuable.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Staves of Elemental Mastery:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The epic essentially consumes <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>three</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> staves, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Earth</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Water</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> directly, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Air</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> indirectly.  It might be nice to decouple them, but is it critical?  The recent pet changes dwarf the effect of the staves.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Earlier Mana Regeneration:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Simply adding a second charge to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Rod of Modulation</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, as argued in <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showMessage?topicID=1190.topic">PROPOSAL: Mini T-Rods</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, and adding one charge net-mana rod in the 30's would extend the capabilities of rodding down to lower levels.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Resists on Rains:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Until I got <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Shock of Fiery Blades</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I always tried to take advantage of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Sirroco</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> whenever possible.  I have had no problem with rains.  I also make a habit of casting a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Malosi</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->-type spell early, usually pulling with it.  I have had no problems with resists on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Sirroco</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Post 50 nukes:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
These have always seemed adequate to me, the only missing pieces at 60 might be an upgrade to the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Shock of Steel</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> line, MR not FR, and a better <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  PBAoE</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  A <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  PBAoE</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> version of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Malosi</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would also be sweet.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Conclusion:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I think we are nearly fixed, and most of what remains is properly pet-centered.<br>
